<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1888,2023]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1888,1915]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum rounded, directed forwards, anterior margin of median carina concave before the crest, few small denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[813,900,1925,1951]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1947,1972]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lophotettix brevicristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491594/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) (less than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[1056,1219,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Lophotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alticristatus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1219,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">L. alticristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); median carina almost straight and with two small ripples (
<figureCitation box="[610,697,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1947,1972]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lophotettix brevicristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491594/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
, dorsal view); femur robust and with lappets throughout on dorsal, ventral and external margins (
<figureCitation box="[486,601,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1947,1972]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lophotettix brevicristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491594/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 3A,B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
